race.description: Starter Mr Rex Kelly Rip Country Boosted Mdn Hcp
race.comment: MCCOSKER (1) looks hard to beat in a plain maiden. Has only raced twice, filling a minor placing on each occasion. Came from well back to be beaten just over a length last start over 1420m here. Needs this trip now and looks ready to win. TRAVELLER (10) is a lightly raced seven-year-old who produced a career-best performance last time out when he closed strongly to get up for third over 1410m at Lismore. Will enjoy getting out to this trip and is going better than most of these so he must be respected. EINSTEIN'S THEORY (2) raced beyond a mile for the first time last start and wasn't beaten far at Port Macquarie. Will benefit from that hit-out and looks one of the better chances. KENDYACATCHME (7) has had plenty of chances but does have a couple placings here from three attempts so cannot be dismissed entirely. MAHUIKA MAROI (8) strips fitter and can improve on a moderate first-up effort at Port Macquarie.
